From: XR500v OpenWrt project
Subject: [PATCH] i2c: mt7621: allow selection on ECONET

The EN751221 contains an MT7621-compatible I2C controller.

Based on Benjamin Larsson's econet-eth-mainline work.
--- a/drivers/i2c/busses/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/i2c/busses/Kconfig
@@ -905,7 +905,7 @@ config I2C_MV64XXX
 
 config I2C_MT7621
 	tristate "MT7621/MT7628 I2C Controller"
-	depends on (RALINK && (SOC_MT7620 || SOC_MT7621)) || ARCH_AIROHA || COMPILE_TEST
+	depends on (RALINK && (SOC_MT7620 || SOC_MT7621)) || ARCH_AIROHA || ECONET || COMPILE_TEST
 	help
 	  Say Y here to include support for I2C controller in the
 	  MediaTek MT7621/MT7628 SoCs.
